article.description: — Darius Maddox had 18 points in George Mason's 64-46 victory over Richmond on Saturday.
article.headline: Maddox's 18 lead George Mason over Richmond 64-46
article.linkText: Maddox's 18 lead George Mason over Richmond 64-46
article.story: FAIRFAX, Va. -- — Darius Maddox had 18 points in George Mason's 64-46 victory over Richmond on Saturday. Maddox went 7 of 9 from the field (3 for 4 from 3-point range) for the Patriots (20-11, 9-9 Atlantic 10 Conference). Amari Kelly scored 14 points and added seven rebounds. Woody Newton went 5 of 12 from the field (2 for 4 from 3-point range) to finish with 12 points, while adding 11 rebounds. The Spiders (23-8, 15-3) were led in scoring by Isaiah Bigelow and Neal Quinn, who each finished with 11 points. Dji Bailey had eight points and two steals. The Spiders broke a six-game winning streak with the loss. George Mason took the lead with 5:15 remaining in the first half and did not relinquish it. The score was 29-24 at halftime, with Maddox racking up 11 points. George Mason extended its lead to 60-40 during the second half, fueled by a 15-2 scoring run. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
